<paper id="1973874773"><title>SELS: a secure e-mail list service</title><year>2005</year><authors><author org="University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign" id="2066412529">Himanshu Khurana</author><author org="University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign" id="2006362061">Adam Slagell</author><author org="University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign" id="2115161840">Rafael Bonilla</author></authors><n_citation>30</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>19438344</reference><reference>126735607</reference><reference>1503064432</reference><reference>1585096027</reference><reference>1588182391</reference><reference>1590823599</reference><reference>1601379374</reference><reference>1805165030</reference><reference>1836012993</reference><reference>1964909769</reference><reference>1967350389</reference><reference>2019267322</reference><reference>2054251041</reference><reference>2085302848</reference><reference>2086042811</reference><reference>2105861506</reference><reference>2107863397</reference><reference>2144415270</reference><reference>2151349068</reference><reference>2153326378</reference><reference>2159945176</reference></references><venue id="2754781246" type="C">ACM Symposium on Applied Computing</venue><doi>10.1145/1066677.1066752</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.45414">World Wide Web</keyword><keyword weight="0.50525">Authentication</keyword><keyword weight="0.47512">Confidentiality</keyword><keyword weight="0.56673">Mailing list</keyword><keyword weight="0.42013">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.45032">Computer security</keyword><keyword weight="0.40453">Eudora</keyword><keyword weight="0.48434">Java</keyword><keyword weight="0.45112">Private information retrieval</keyword><keyword weight="0.47511">Spamming</keyword></keywords><publisher>ACM</publisher><abstract>Exchange of private information content among a large number of users via E-mail List Services is becoming increasingly common. In this paper we address security requirements in that setting and develop a new protocol, SELS (a Secure E-mail List Service) that provides confidentiality, integrity, and authentication for e-mails exchanged via lists. In addition, SELS also protects against the use of lists for e-mail spamming. We have developed a prototype of SELS in Java, and integrated it with the Eudora e-mail client.</abstract></paper>